args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hr</span> : <span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">r</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h₁f₁</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Meromorphic/Basic.html#Meromorphic\">Meromorphic</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₁</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h₂f₁</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">z</span> : <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Meromorphic/Order.html#meromorphicOrderAt\">meromorphicOrderAt</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">z</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h₁f₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Meromorphic/Basic.html#Meromorphic\">Meromorphic</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₂</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h₂f₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">z</span> : <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Meromorphic/Order.html#meromorphicOrderAt\">meromorphicOrderAt</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">z</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.html#ValueDistribution.logCounting\">logCounting</a> (<span class=\"fn\">f₁</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₂</span>) <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <span class=\"fn\">r</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.html#ValueDistribution.logCounting\">logCounting</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.html#ValueDistribution.logCounting\">logCounting</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span>) <span class=\"fn\">r</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"**Alias** of `ValueDistribution.logCounting_mul_zero_le`.\n\n---\n\nFor `1 ≤ r`, the logarithmis counting function for the zeros of `f * g` is less than or equal to the\nsum of the logarithmic counting functions for the zeros of `f` and `g`, respectively.\n\nNote: The statement proven here is found at the top of page 169 of [Lang: Introduction to Complex\nHyperbolic Spaces](https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007/978-1-4757-1945-1) where it is written as\nan inequality between functions. This could be interpreted as claiming that the inequality holds for\nALL values of `r`, which is not true. For a counterexample, take `f₁ : z → z` and `f₂ : z → z⁻¹`.\nThen,\n\n- `logCounting f₁ 0 = log`\n- `logCounting f₂ 0 = 0`\n- `logCounting (f₁ * f₂) 0 = 0`\n\nBut `log r` is negative for small `r`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.html#ValueDistribution.logCounting_zero_mul_le","kind":"theorem","line":469,"name":"ValueDistribution.logCounting_zero_mul_le","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.lean#L469-L469"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.html#ValueDistribution.logCounting_mul_zero_le\"><span class=\"name\">ValueDistribution</span>.<span class=\"name\">logCounting_mul_zero_le</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Field/Basic.html#NontriviallyNormedField\">NontriviallyNormedField</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ProperSpace.html#ProperSpace\">ProperSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">f₁ </span><span class=\"fn\">f₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> → <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">r</span> : <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Real/Basic.html#Real\">ℝ</a>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hr</span> : <span class=\"fn\">1</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">r</span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h₁f₁</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Meromorphic/Basic.html#Meromorphic\">Meromorphic</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₁</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h₂f₁</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">z</span> : <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Meromorphic/Order.html#meromorphicOrderAt\">meromorphicOrderAt</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">z</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h₁f₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Meromorphic/Basic.html#Meromorphic\">Meromorphic</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₂</span></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">h₂f₂</span> : <span class=\"fn\">∀ (<span class=\"fn\">z</span> : <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span>), <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Meromorphic/Order.html#meromorphicOrderAt\">meromorphicOrderAt</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">z</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Ne\">≠</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Order/Notation.html#Top.top\">⊤</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.html#ValueDistribution.logCounting\">logCounting</a> (<span class=\"fn\">f₁</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HMul.hMul\">*</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₂</span>) <span class=\"fn\">0</span> <span class=\"fn\">r</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.html#ValueDistribution.logCounting\">logCounting</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₁</span> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HAdd.hAdd\">+</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.html#ValueDistribution.logCounting\">logCounting</a> <span class=\"fn\">f₂</span> <span class=\"fn\">0</span></span>) <span class=\"fn\">r</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"For `1 ≤ r`, the logarithmis counting function for the zeros of `f * g` is less than or equal to the\nsum of the logarithmic counting functions for the zeros of `f` and `g`, respectively.\n\nNote: The statement proven here is found at the top of page 169 of [Lang: Introduction to Complex\nHyperbolic Spaces](https://link.springer.com/book/10.1007/978-1-4757-1945-1) where it is written as\nan inequality between functions. This could be interpreted as claiming that the inequality holds for\nALL values of `r`, which is not true. For a counterexample, take `f₁ : z → z` and `f₂ : z → z⁻¹`.\nThen,\n\n- `logCounting f₁ 0 = log`\n- `logCounting f₂ 0 = 0`\n- `logCounting (f₁ * f₂) 0 = 0`\n\nBut `log r` is negative for small `r`.\n","docLink":"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.html#ValueDistribution.logCounting_mul_zero_le","kind":"theorem","line":443,"name":"ValueDistribution.logCounting_mul_zero_le","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.lean#L443-L467"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Complex/ValueDistribution/LogCounting/Basic.html#ValueDistribution.logCounting_sum_top_eventuallyLE\"><span class=\"name\">ValueDistribution</span>.<span class=\"name\">logCounting_sum_top_eventuallyLE</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Analysis/Normed/Field/Basic.html#NontriviallyNormedField\">NontriviallyNormedField</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/MetricSpace/ProperSpace.html#ProperSpace\">ProperSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">𝕜</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a h